The paper focuses on contention resolution for matroid constraints, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the connection between contention resolution and the secretary problem, which is a classic problem in decision theory and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper involves optimization and constrained optimization problems, which are studied in the categories of game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves the study of distributions and correlations, which are studied in the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
